Having regard to the Treaties establishing the European Communities, and in particular Article 162 of the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Whereas on 8 February 1994 the Commission adopted Decision 94/90/ECSC, EEC, Euratom (1) on public access to Commission documents;
Whereas that Decision provided for a fee to be charged for copies of printed documents exceeding 30 sheets;
Whereas the current system has proved difficult to implement in practice and not very efficient;
Whereas accordingly the system of payment of a fee should be made optional,
